Dear Dr Mohammed,


Thanks for the clarifications.  With regards to this point:

=20

=E2=80=9C=C2=B7         You will start with the standard allocation, 2TB  project dir=
ectory on the high-speed filesystem, and 50Gb on home directory. According t=
o our estimation, this will allow me to run a batch of 5 samples only, then =
I will have to copy the output back to BTC server and clear the  analysis on=
 HPC, and upload another batch of 5 samples and so on. It will work yet it w=
ill be slow since the batch I have now has 95 samples for WES analysis.  =E2=80=9C

=20

My suggestion would be, to get started on the HPC, get an estimate for how =
much time is required to finish analysis for a sample, and how much storage =
is required for a single sample; we can then agree on a reasonable number of=
 samples  that you can analyze simultaneously, and we can allocate the appro=
priate amount of storage for an agreed length of time. The HPC is new and re=
latively free, so you should be able to get your work through quickly. I wou=
ld also like to point out that we also  provide scientific computing support=
, and so can help with getting your workload to get through the system quick=
er.

=20

Thanks,

Dureid

