Dear Dr. Dureid=20

=20

It was great to meet you today. Kindly find my reply to the following point=
s:

=20
Data storage; Current situation=20
The BTC server is in the BTC lab on main campus
Was purchased in 2017 and is likely out of support/maintenance.
We discussed the possibility of moving to a more centralized model, where r=
esources are provided and managed centrally by research computing.
It is connected as the storage for the output of the 4 sequencing machines =
at BTC. Also, been used for data analysis since all tools are installed in B=
TC server.=20
The sequencing machines output data to the BTC when it is required, and thi=
s is generally when you have a specific project or group of samples. As an e=
stimate this is ~350GB at a time, every few weeks or  when required. This va=
ries based on the project status and if we have any urgent request for analy=
sis=20
It is running out of storage; it has a total of 55TB and currently only 4TB=
 are free
=C2=B7        Majority of space is consumed by intermediate files generated by =
the analysis pipelines

=C2=B7        Dr Mohammed will explore removing some of the intermediate files,=
 to see if he can carry on with the analysis. I managed to free 5 TB, so we =
have around 9TB now
I suggested that you create project and account on the HPC to get started o=
n your current analysis.
=C2=B7        You will start with the standard allocation, 2TB project director=
y on the high-speed filesystem, and 50Gb on home directory. According to our=
 estimation, this will allow me to run a batch of 5 samples only, then I wil=
l have to copy the output back to BTC server and clear the analysis on HPC, =
and upload another batch of 5 samples and so on. It will work yet  it will b=
e slow since the batch I have now has 95 samples for WES analysis. =20

=C2=B7        If this proves inadequate, we will adjust as necessary. I am happ=
y to explore this option
Storage purchased previously by Dr Habiba, was around 125 TB, of which ~80T=
B is currently utilized.
=C2=B7        We discussed that the previous purchase was for hardware, which h=
as a limited lifetime and needs to be refreshed periodically

=C2=B7        I suggested that we try to move to purchasing storage as a servic=
e, where the storage can persist over multiple hardware refreshes. Dr. Habib=
a can confirm this!=20
We will arrange another meeting to discuss how best to move forward with th=
e storage.=20
Dragen Server=20
Is comprised of specialized hardware and software for genomic analysis
You have purchased installation and support from local company, Purehealth.=
 This does not include Sysadmin support
Will need to mount/connect it to the 4 sequencers in BTC. Could be more or =
less depend on other pipelines or machines that we may need to use in future=
=20
Needs to be installed in a data center, as it is not suitable for a lab env=
ironment.
=20

