put back to BTC server and clear the
 analysis on HPC, and upload another batch of 5 samples and so on. It will =
work yet it will be slow since the batch I have now has 95 samples for WES a=
nalysis.</span><span style=3D"color:black">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span style=3D"col=
or:black">=E2=80=9C</span><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">My suggestion would be, to get started on the HPC, get=
 an estimate for how much time is required to finish analysis for a sample, =
and how much storage is required for a single sample; we can then agree on a=
 reasonable number of samples
 that you can analyze simultaneously, and we can allocate the appropriate a=
mount of storage for an agreed length of time. The HPC is new and relatively=
 free, so you should be able to get your work through quickly. I would also =
like to point out that we also
 provide scientific computing support, and so can help with getting your wo=
rkload to get through the system quicker.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">Thanks,<o:p></o:p></p>
