<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"color:#1F497D">Dear Dr. Dureid <o:p></o:p=
></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"color:#1F497D"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></=
p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"color:#1F497D">It was great to meet you t=
oday. Kindly find my reply to the following points:<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"color:#1F497D"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></=
p>
<ol style=3D"margin-top:0in" start=3D"1" type=3D"1">
<li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-list:l1 level1 lfo3">Data storage; Current=
 situation
<o:p></o:p>
<ul style=3D"margin-top:0in" type=3D"disc">
<li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-list:l1 level2 lfo3">The BTC server is in =
the BTC lab on main campus<o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-l=
ist:l1 level2 lfo3">Was purchased in 2017 and is likely out of support/maint=
enance.<o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-list:l1 level2 lfo3"=
>We discussed the possibility of moving to a more centralized model, where r=
esources are provided and managed centrally by research computing.<o:p></o:p=
></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-list:l1 level2 lfo3">It is connected =
as the storage for the output of the 4 sequencing machines at BTC.
<span style=3D"color:red">Also, been used for data analysis since all tools a=
re installed in BTC server.
</span><o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-list:l1 level2 lfo3=
">The sequencing machines output data to the BTC when it is required, and th=
is is generally when you have a specific project or group of samples. As an =
estimate this is ~350GB at a time, every few weeks or
 when required. <span style=3D"color:red">This varies based on the project st=
atus and if we have any urgent request for analysis
</span><o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-list:l1 level2 lfo3=
">It is running out of storage; it has a total of 55TB and currently only 4T=
B are free<o:p></o:p></li></ul>
</li></ol>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"margin-left:117.0pt;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list=
:l1 level3 lfo3">
<![if !supportLists]><span style=3D"font-family:Symbol"><span style=3D"mso-list=
:Ignore">=C2=B7<span style=3D"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;=
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span dir=3D"LTR"></span>Majority of space is =
consumed by intermediate files generated by the analysis pipelines<o:p></o:p=
></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"margin-left:117.0pt;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list=
:l1 level3 lfo3">
<![if !supportLists]><span style=3D"font-family:Symbol"><span style=3D"mso-list=
:Ignore">=C2=B7<span style=3D"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;=
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span dir=3D"LTR"></span>Dr Mohammed will expl=
ore removing some of the intermediate files, to see if he can carry on with =
the analysis.
<span style=3D"color:red">I managed to free 5 TB, so we have around 9TB now</=
span><o:p></o:p></p>
<ol style=3D"margin-top:0in" start=3D"1" type=3D"1">
<ul style=3D"margin-top:0in" type=3D"disc">
<li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-list:l1 level2 lfo3">I suggested that you =
create project and account on the HPC to get started on your current analysi=
s.<o:p></o:p></li></ul>
</ol>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"margin-left:117.0pt;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list=
:l1 level3 lfo3">
<![if !supportLists]><span style=3D"font-family:Symbol"><span style=3D"mso-list=
:Ignore">=C2=B7<span style=3D"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;=
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span dir=3D"LTR"></span>You will start with t=
he standard allocation, 2TB project directory on the high-speed filesystem, =
and 50Gb on home directory.
<span style=3D"color:red">According to our estimation, this will allow me to =
run a batch of 5 samples only, then I will have to copy the output back to B=
TC server and clear the analysis on HPC, and upload another batch of 5 sampl=
es and so on. It will work yet
 it will be slow since the batch I have now has 95 samples for WES analysis=
.</span> &nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"margin-left:117.0pt;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list=
:l1 level3 lfo3">
<![if !supportLists]><span style=3D"font-family:Symbol"><span style=3D"mso-list=
:Ignore">=C2=B7<span style=3D"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;=
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span dir=3D"LTR"></span>If this proves inadeq=
uate, we will adjust as necessary.
<span style=3D"color:red">I am happy to explore this option</span><o:p></o:p>=
</p>
<ol style=3D"margin-top:0in" start=3D"1" type=3D"1">
<ul style=3D"margin-top:0in" type=3D"disc">
<li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-list:l1 level2 lfo3">Storage purchased pre=
viously by Dr Habiba, was around 125 TB, of which ~80TB is currently utilize=
d.<o:p></o:p></li></ul>
</ol>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"margin-left:117.0pt;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list=
:l1 level3 lfo3">
<![if !supportLists]><span style=3D"font-family:Symbol"><span style=3D"mso-list=
:Ignore">=C2=B7<span style=3D"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;=
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span dir=3D"LTR"></span>We discussed that the=
 previous purchase was for hardware, which has a limited lifetime and needs =
to be refreshed periodically<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"margin-left:117.0pt;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list=
:l1 level3 lfo3">
<![if !supportLists]><span style=3D"font-family:Symbol"><span style=3D"mso-list=
:Ignore">=C2=B7<span style=3D"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;=
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span dir=3D"LTR"></span>I suggested that we t=
ry to move to purchasing storage as a service, where the storage can persist=
 over multiple hardware refreshes.
<span style=3D"color:red">Dr. Habiba can confirm this! </span><o:p></o:p></p>
<ol style=3D"margin-top:0in" start=3D"1" type=3D"1">
<ul style=3D"margin-top:0in" type=3D"disc">
<li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-list:l1 level2 lfo3">We will arrange anoth=
er meeting to discuss how best to move forward with the storage.
<o:p></o:p></li></ul>
<li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-list:l1 level1 lfo3">Dragen Server <o:p></=
o:p>
<ul style=3D"margin-top:0in" type=3D"disc">
<li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-list:l1 level2 lfo3">Is comprised of speci=
alized hardware and software for genomic analysis<o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"=
MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-list:l1 level2 lfo3">You have purchased installation a=
nd support from local company, Purehealth. This does not include Sysadmin su=
pport<o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-list:l1 level2 lfo3">W=
ill need to mount/connect it to the 4 sequencers in BTC.
<span style=3D"color:red">Could be more or less depend on other pipelines or =
machines that we may need to use in future
</span><o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-list:l1 level2 lfo3=
">Needs to be installed in a data center, as it is not suitable for a lab en=
vironment.<o:p></o:p></li></ul>
</li></ol>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"color:#1F497D"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></=
p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"color:#1F497D"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></=
